ay-gradient":""}},"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[4],"tags":[416,13,465,82,157,159,114,273,396,537],"class_list":["post-32911","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-righteousness-al-birr","tag-agreed-upon-muttafaqun-alayhi","tag-forgiveness-al-maghfirah","tag-good-deeds-hasanat","tag-gratitude-al-shukr","tag-harm-al-darar","tag-hereafter-akhirah","tag-manners-adab","tag-reward-al-ajr","tag-roads","tag-trees"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-8yP","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":225,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2010\/12\/02\/the-roads-have-rights\/","url_meta":{"origin":32911,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Rights: Roads have rights, so fulfill their rights","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 2, 2010","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Sa\u2019id al-Khudri reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cBeware of loitering in the roads.\u201d They said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, we have nowhere else to sit and talk.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cIf you insist, then give the road its rights.\u201d They said, \u201cWhat\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":6302,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/12\/faith-branches-modesty\/","url_meta":{"origin":32911,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Faith: True Iman has sixty branches, including modesty","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 12, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cFaith has sixty to seventy branches, the best of which is to declare there is no God but Allah, the least of which is to remove something harmful from the road, and modesty is a branch\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":9806,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/11\/14\/every-joint-charity-due\/","url_meta":{"origin":32911,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Sadaqa: Every joint has charity due, even a good word","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 14, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cCharity is due upon every joint of the people for every day upon which the sun rises. Justly reconciling two people is charity. Helping a man with his animal and lifting his luggage upon it is\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":640,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/03\/19\/be-determined-in-your-dua\/","url_meta":{"origin":32911,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Dua: Be determined, certain in your supplications","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 19, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said,\u00a0\u201cWhen one of you calls upon Allah, let him be determined in the supplication and he should not say, 'O Allah, give me if You will,' for there is no one to coerce Allah.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25557,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/06\/mercy-believers-cursed\/","url_meta":{"origin":32911,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Curses: O Allah, have mercy on believers I cursed","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 6, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cO Allah, I am only a human being. Whenever I scold, curse, or punish a Muslim man, then turn it into purification and mercy for him.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 6361, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2601 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32976,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/07\/30\/forgives-between-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":32911,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Allah forgives what one did between prayers","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 30, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Uthman ibn Affan reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cA Muslim man does not perform ablution in an excellent manner and then performs prayer, but that Allah will forgive him for what occurred between his prayer and the next.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 158, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u064